Accuracy of the habitat categorization was assessed with validation datasets comprising: 
1) independent telemetry locations from the remaining, unused 10% of the sample sets from subregion resource selection modeling (RSF); 
2) telemetry locations from regions that did not meet sample size criteria (i.e., non-RSF subregions); 
3) lek locations. 
Because the number of telemetry locations collected for individual birds varied among study sites (e.g. VHF vs. GPS), we calculated the proportion of validation locations falling within habitat categories for each unique bird, and then averaged those proportions across all birds.
Averages were then compared to a normal distribution with expected values based on standard deviations (expected high = 69.1%, moderate=15.0%, low=9.2%, none=6.7%). We found that all three datasets exceeded observed validation values from Coates et al. 2014.
